item.title: Aryan - Hacked Version?
item.dc:creator: @Krichevskoy Krichevskoy
item.description:
@Krichevskoy wrote:

HDKilla:

Not saying im paying for another version of Aryan, but if its deobbed, then thats half the battle to a new bot, isnt it?

No, it isn’t. It is, perhaps, a scant beginning at best.
Why doesn’t anyone get it? Past paradigms in ‘botmaking’ are comepletely useless now.
Even if you have the source, you can’t use it. Every change you make to the client, even (possibly) recompiling source, makes you more detectable. If you really want instructions, the way forward is to use the client for information then generate human-like input. It might mean that your bots are a little bit less lucrative than before, but it also means that you won’t get your ass banned the second you log in.

Read full topic
